{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862184480,"sessionID":"ses_2865de249ffe6HkFMq7rwvY7jn","part":{"id":"prt_d79a276bc001XY7pIcxepGbGSz","messageID":"msg_d79a26202001L94JH0NrBkm96y","sessionID":"ses_2865de249ffe6HkFMq7rwvY7jn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_96f95ea13a1840809dbd5124","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that builds a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default), with optional proxy configuration and version tagging derived from metadata.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack, build, publish, invoke, and status. The `build` command is the second step, creating Docker images from packed workspaces before publish/deployment.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Implement the `build` command that:\n16: 1. Loads workspace metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n17: 2. Validates build prerequisites (Docker availability)\n18: 3. Determines build mode (local vs cloud)\n19: 4. Auto-increments version before build\n20: 5. Executes local Docker build\n21: 6. Updates metadata with build results\n22: \n23: ### Value\n24: \n25: - **Containerization**: Creates deployable Docker images from agent code\n26: - **Versioning**: Auto-increments semantic versions for tracking\n27: - **Integration**: Works seamlessly with `pack` and `publish` commands\n28: - **Consistency**: Follows existing CLI patterns and design specs\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## Scope\n33: \n34: ### In-Scope\n35: \n36: | Component | Path | Description |\n37: |-----------|------|-------------|\n38: | Build command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n39: | Build runtime | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Core build logic |\n40: | Docker service | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Docker SDK integration |\n41: | Metadata models | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | AgentMetadata (existing) |\n42: \n43: ### CLI Interface\n44: \n45: ```python\n46: def build(\n47:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n48:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n49:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n50:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n51:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n52: ) -> None:\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ### BuildRuntime API\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: class BuildRuntime:\n59:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n60:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n61:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n62:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n63:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n64:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n65:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### Out-of-Scope\n69: \n70: - Cloud build implementation (placeholder only)\n71: - Publishing built images to registries\n72: - Interactive prompts\n73: - Build from scratch without prior `pack`\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Impact Analysis\n78: \n79: ### Dependencies\n80: \n81: | Dependency | Purpose |\n82: |------------|---------|\n83: | `docker>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python |\n84: | `semver>=3.0.0` | Semantic version handling |\n85: | `packaging>=23.0` | Version parsing |\n86: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n87: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich terminal output |\n88: \n89: ### Upstream\n90: \n91: - **cli-toolkit/design.md** — BuildRuntime class design\n92: - **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Build command requirements and scenarios\n93: - **AR-020 (pack)** — Requires packed workspace as input\n94: \n95: ### Downstream Consumers\n96: \n97: 1. **Publish command** — Uses built image for deployment\n98: 2. **End users** — Second CLI command in agent workflow\n99: \n100: ### Risks\n101: \n102: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n103: |------|----------|------------|\n104: | Docker not available | High | Early validation with clear error |\n105: | Build timeout | Medium | Configurable timeout, proxy support |\n106: | Version format issues | Low | Use semver library, validate on load |\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## Alternatives Considered\n111: \n112: ### Option 1: Inline Build Logic (Not Selected)\n113: \n114: **Approach**: Implement all build logic directly in CLI main file.\n115: \n116: **Pros**:\n117: - Simpler initial implementation\n118: - Direct function calls\n119: \n120: **Cons**:\n121: - Violates separation of concerns\n122: - Harder to test\n123: - Duplicated logic patterns\n124: \n125: **Decision**: Not selected — violates project architecture patterns.\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ### Option 2: BuildRuntime Class (Selected)\n130: \n131: **Approach**: Dedicated BuildRuntime class following existing patterns.\n132: \n133: **Pros**:\n134: - Consistent with PublishRuntime, InvokeRuntime patterns\n135: - Clean separation of concerns\n136: - Testable unit components\n137: - Reusable across CLI and other entry points\n138: \n139: **Cons**:\n140: - More initial code\n141: \n142: **Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and design specs.\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ### Option 3: Cloud-First Build (Not Selected)\n147: \n148: **Approach**: Default to cloud builds, local Docker as fallback.\n149: \n150: **Pros**:\n151: - No local Docker dependency\n152: - Consistent with cloud-native workflows\n153: \n154: **Cons**:\n155: - Requires cloud credentials\n156: - Slower feedback loop\n157: - Spec requires local-first default\n158: \n159: **Decision**: Not selected — spec requires local build as default.\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Implementation Plan\n164: \n165: ### Phase 1: Core BuildRuntime\n166: - [ ] Enhance existing BuildRuntime class\n167: - [ ] Implement `_validate_build_prerequisites()`\n168: - [ ] Implement `_build_local()` with DockerService\n169: - [ ] Implement version increment logic\n170: \n171: ### Phase 2: Metadata Integration\n172: - [ ] Load workspace metadata via MetadataService\n173: - [ ] Update metadata with build results\n174: - [ ] Implement version rollback on failure\n175: \n176: ### Phase 3: CLI Integration\n177: - [ ] Add build command to main.py Typer app\n178: - [ ] Implement Rich progress indicators\n179: - [ ] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n180: \n181: ### Phase 4: Testing\n182: - [ ] Unit tests for BuildRuntime methods\n183: - [ ] Integration tests with Docker\n184: - [ ] CLI argument parsing tests\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Acceptance Criteria\n189: \n190: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n191: |----|----------|-----------------|\n192: | AC-001 | Valid workspace with metadata, local build mode | Image built successfully |\n193: | AC-002 | Docker not available | RuntimeError with clear message |\n194: | AC-003 | Nonexistent workspace path | ValueError raised |\n195: | AC-004 | Version increment (X.Y.Z) | Patch version incremented |\n196: | AC-005 | Version increment (no version) | Version set to \"0.0.1\" |\n197: | AC-006 | Build failure | Version rolled back, error raised |\n198: | AC-007 | Successful build output | Success message with image details |\n199: | AC-008 | Build with proxy | Proxy passed to Docker build |\n200: | AC-009 | Verbose mode | Detailed logging enabled |\n201: | AC-010 | Cloud build mode | _build_cloud called (placeholder) |\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Technical Design\n206: \n207: ### Version Increment Logic\n208: \n209: Per spec: \"increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`)\"\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> str:\n213:     current = metadata.version\n214:     if not current:\n215:         return \"0.0.1\"\n216:     \n217:     try:\n218:         v = Version(current)\n219:         return str(v.replace(v.major, v.minor, v.micro + 1))\n220:     except Exception:\n221:         # Fallback: append .1 or -1\n222:         if current.endswith(\".1\"):\n223:             parts = current.rsplit(\".\", 1)\n224:             return f\"{parts[0]}.{int(parts[1]) + 1}\"\n225:         return f\"{current}.1\"\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ### Data Flow\n229: \n230: ```\n231: User: kubectl-agentcube build --workspace /path/to/agent\n232:   │\n233:   ├─→ Parse CLI options\n234:   ├─→ Create BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n235:   │\n236:   ├─→ BuildRuntime.build(workspace_path, **options)\n237:   │   │\n238:   │   ├─→ Load metadata via MetadataService\n239:   │   │\n240:   │   ├─→ _validate_build_prerequisites()\n241:   │   │   └─→ DockerService.check_docker_available()\n242:   │   │\n243:   │   ├─→ _increment_version(metadata)\n244:   │   │\n245:   │   ├─→ Determine build mode (local/cloud)\n246:   │   │\n247:   │   ├─→ _build_local() or _build_cloud()\n248:   │   │   └─→ DockerService.build_image()\n249:   │   │\n250:   │   └─→ _update_build_metadata()\n251:   │       └─→ MetadataService.save_metadata()\n252:   │\n253:   └─→ Print success/failure message\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Timeline Estimate\n259: \n260: | Phase | Effort |\n261: |-------|--------|\n262: | Core BuildRuntime | 2-3 hours |\n263: | Metadata Integration | 1-2 hours |\n264: | CLI Integration | 1 hour |\n265: | Testing | 2 hours |\n266: | **Total** | **6-8 hours** |\n\n(End of file - total 266 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that builds a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default), with optional proxy configuration and version tagging derived from metadata.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack, build, publish, invoke, and status. The `build` command is the second step, creating Docker images from packed workspaces before publish/deployment.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement the `build` command that:\n1. Loads workspace metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n2. Validates build prerequisites (Docker availability)\n3. Determines build mode (local vs cloud)\n4. Auto-increments version before build\n5. Executes local Docker build","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775862184467,"end":1775862184477}}}}
