{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862252151,"sessionID":"ses_2865de249ffe6HkFMq7rwvY7jn","part":{"id":"prt_d79a2d8f4001QVpckN1OQKj6Q9","messageID":"msg_d79a2cb64001hnw9dVxr5f94ao","sessionID":"ses_2865de249ffe6HkFMq7rwvY7jn","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_658b527f1b054f9f9c6a5844","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-022 — CLI Publish Command\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that deploys a packaged and built agent to either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack → build → **publish** → invoke → status. The `publish` command is the third step, deploying the built Docker image to the target infrastructure.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement the `publish` command that:\n1. Loads workspace metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n2. Validates prerequisites (provider-specific requirements)\n3. Prepares image URL for publishing\n4. Deploys to the target provider (AgentCube or K8s)\n5. Updates metadata with deployment results\n\n### Value\n\n- **Dual Provider Support**: Deploy to AgentCube CRD or native Kubernetes\n- **Flexible Configuration**: Support for replicas, NodePort, namespace, environment variables\n- **Integration**: Works seamlessly with `pack` and `build` commands\n- **Consistency**: Follows existing CLI patterns and design specs\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| Publish command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n| Publish runtime | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Core publish logic |\n| Kubernetes provider | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | K8s Deployment + Service |\n| AgentCube provider | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CRD |\n| Metadata models | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | AgentMetadata |\n| Tests | `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Unit tests |\n\n### CLI Interface\n\n```python\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL\"),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"NodePort (30000-32767)\"),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas\"),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"Deployment namespace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### PublishRuntime API\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Docker image push to registry (handled by build command)\n- Agent invocation after deployment\n- Interactive deployment prompts\n- Deployment to non-K8s targets (e.g., cloud serverless)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s Python client |\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | Metadata serialization |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich terminal output |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **cli-toolkit/design.md** — PublishRuntime class design\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Publish command requirements and scenarios\n- **AR-020 (pack)** — Requires packed workspace with metadata\n- **AR-021 (build)** — Requires built Docker image\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Invoke command** — Uses published endpoint\n2. **Status command** — Checks deployment status\n3. **End users** — Third CLI command in agent workflow\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| K8s cluster inaccessible | High | Clear error message, mock mode for testing |\n| AgentRuntime CRD not installed | High | Validate CRD existence before deployment |\n| Invalid NodePort range | Medium | Validate 30000-32767 before deployment |\n| Missing required metadata | Medium | Validate router_url, workload_manager_url for agentcube |\n| Deployment timeout | Medium | Configurable timeout, status polling |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Direct K8s API Calls (Not Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Call Kubernetes APIs directly from PublishRuntime without provider abstraction.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler initial implementation\n- Less abstraction overhead\n\n**Cons**:\n- Tight coupling to K8s APIs\n- Harder to test\n- No provider abstraction\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — violates separation of concerns pattern.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Provider Abstraction (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Abstract deployment logic into provider classes (KubernetesProvider, AgentCubeProvider).\n\n**Pros**:\n- Clean separation of concerns\n- Testable with mocks\n- Consistent with K8s operator pattern\n- Easy to extend for new providers\n\n**Cons**:\n- More initial code\n- Requires interface maintenance\n\n**Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and design specs.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Cloud-Native Build & Deploy (Not Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Combine build and publish into single cloud-native workflow.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Fewer CLI commands\n- Cloud-native workflow\n\n**Cons**:\n- Violates spec (separate build/publish)\n- Less flexibility\n- Harder to debug\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — spec requires separate build and publish commands.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core PublishRuntime\n- [x] Implement `_prepare_image_for_publishing()`\n- [x] Implement `_publish_k8s()` with KubernetesProvider\n- [x] Implement `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` with AgentCubeProvider\n\n### Phase 2: Metadata Integration\n- [x] Load workspace metadata via MetadataService\n- [x] Update metadata with deployment results\n- [x] Handle agent_id and endpoint tracking\n\n### Phase 3: CLI Integration\n- [x] Add publish command to main.py Typer app\n- [x] Implement Rich progress indicators\n- [x] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n\n### Phase 4: Validation & Refinement\n- [ ] Validate router_url/workload_manager_url for agentcube provider\n- [ ] Add NodePort range validation\n- [ ] Improve endpoint URL for K8s NodePort access\n- [ ] Handle image pull secrets\n\n### Phase 5: Testing\n- [x] Unit tests for PublishRuntime methods\n- [ ] Integration tests with K8s cluster\n- [ ] CLI argument parsing tests\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| AC-001 | Valid workspace, agentcube provider | AgentRuntime CR deployed |\n| AC-002 | Valid workspace, k8s provider | Deployment + Service created |\n| AC-003 | NodePort out of range | ValueError raised |\n| AC-004 | Missing router_url for agentcube | ValueError raised |\n| AC-005 | Successful deploy | Metadata updated with agent_id |\n| AC-006 | AgentCube deploy | Endpoint points to cluster.local |\n| AC-007 | K8s deploy with NodePort | Service type NodePort |\n| AC-008 | K8s deploy with replicas | Replica count matches |\n| AC-009 | Custom namespace | Resources created in namespace |\n| AC-010 | Verbose mode | Detailed logging enabled |\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### Provider Selection Logic\n\n```python\ndef publish(self, workspace_path: str, provider: str = \"agentcube\", **options):\n    workspace = Path(workspace_path).resolve()\n    metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace)\n\n    # Validate prerequisites\n    if provider == \"agentcube\":\n        if not metadata.router_url or not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"AgentCube provider requires router_url and workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\"\n            )\n        result = self._publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace, metadata, **options)\n    else:\n        result = self._publish_k8s(workspace, metadata, **options)\n\n    # Update metadata\n    metadata.agent_id = result.get(\"agent_id\") or result.get(\"deployment\")\n    metadata.agent_endpoint = result.get(\"endpoint\")\n    self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace, metadata)\n\n    return result\n```\n\n### K8s Provider Flow\n\n```\n_publish_k8s()\n  │\n  ├─→ Create KubernetesProvider(namespace)\n  │\n  ├─→ Prepare image URL\n  │   └─→ _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n  │\n  ├─→ Validate NodePort (30000-32767)\n  │\n  ├─→ KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()\n  │   ├─→ Create Deployment (replicas, env vars)\n  │   ├─→ Create Service (NodePort or ClusterIP)\n  │   └─→ Return endpoint\n  │\n  └─→ Update metadata\n```\n\n### AgentCube Provider Flow\n\n```\n_publish_cr_to_k8s()\n  │\n  ├─→ Create AgentCubeProvider(namespace)\n  │\n  ├─→ Prepare image URL\n  │\n  ├─→ AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()\n  │   ├─→ Create AgentRuntime CR\n  │   │   ├─→ CR Group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n  │   │   ├─→ CR Version: v1alpha1\n  │   │   └─→ Spec: sessionTimeout=15m, maxSessionDuration=8h\n  │   └─→ Return endpoint\n  │\n  └─→ Update metadata\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime CR Structure\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: <agent_name>\n  namespace: <namespace>\nspec:\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  targetPorts:\n    - port: <port>\n      protocol: HTTP\n      name: http\n  podTemplate:\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: agent\n          image: <image_url>\n          resources:\n            limits:\n              cpu: \"1\"\n              memory: \"1Gi\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| Core PublishRuntime | 2-3 hours |\n| Provider Implementation | 2-3 hours |\n| Metadata Integration | 1 hour |\n| CLI Integration | 1 hour |\n| Testing | 2-3 hours |\n| **Total** | **8-12 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Existing Implementation Status\n\nThe publish command has been implemented with the following components:\n\n1. **PublishRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`): 255 lines, implements image preparation, K8s and AgentCube deployment flows\n2. **KubernetesProvider** (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`): 289 lines, creates Deployment + Service with NodePort support\n3. **AgentCubeProvider** (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`): 214 lines, creates AgentRuntime CRD\n4. **CLI binding** (`agentcube/cli/main.py`): Lines 270-390, Typer command with Rich output\n\n### Gaps to Address\n\n1. **Missing validation**: AgentCube provider should validate router_url and workload_manager_url presence\n2. **Endpoint improvement**: K8s NodePort endpoint should return `http://localhost:{node_port}` for easier access\n3. **Image pull secrets**: AgentRuntime should support imagePullSecrets\n4. **Wait for ready**: K8s provider should call `wait_for_deployment_ready()` after deployment\n5. **Pre-publish image push**: Image should be pushed to registry before deployment (optional)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tests/test_publish_runtime.py\">\nERROR [78:64] Expected 2 positional arguments\nERROR [109:70] Expected 2 positional arguments\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/cli/main.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tests/test_publish_runtime.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":77,"character":63},"end":{"line":77,"character":65}},"message":"Expected 2 positional arguments","severity":1,"code":"reportCallIssue","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportCallIssue"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":108,"character":69},"end":{"line":108,"character":71}},"message":"Expected 2 positional arguments","severity":1,"code":"reportCallIssue","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportCallIssue"}}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775862252091,"end":1775862252146}}}}
